# Little Learners

A free, open-source collection of browser-based educational games for young kids (ages 4–7). No installs, no accounts, no cost — just open a page and play.

**Play it live:** `https://YOUR-USERNAME.github.io/bloom-and-count/`
*(replace `YOUR-USERNAME` with your actual GitHub username)*

## Games

| Game | What kids practice |
|---|---|
| 🌸 **Bloom & Count** | Counting and simple addition, set in a garden scene |
| 🏃 **Green Light Dash** | Reflexes and focus, inspired by the classic "Red Light, Green Light" |
| 👻 **Ghost's Star Maze** | Puzzle-solving and planning, with a fog-of-war maze that regenerates every round |
| 🪄 **Word Wizard** | Spelling and vocabulary, guessing words letter by letter across categories |

## Tech

Each game is a single self-contained HTML file — no build tools, no dependencies to install, no backend. Just HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript. Open any file directly in a browser and it works.

## Running it locally

Clone the repo and open `index.html` in your browser:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/bloom-and-count.git
cd bloom-and-count
open index.html
```

